					<common:class level="1">Other non-renewable fuels</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Non-renewable resources are natural substances that are not replenished at the same rate as they are consumed, making them finite. These resources are formed through natural processes such as the decomposition of organic matter or nuclear reactions within the Earth. They include minerals, gems, and energy sources like oil, coal, and natural gas, which are limited in quantity and cannot be naturally regenerated. Other non-renewables include nuclear fuels and metal ores.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">不可再生资源是自然物质，它们的补充速度与消耗速度不同，因此是有限的。这些资源是通过自然过程形成的，例如有机物质的分解或地球内部的核反应。它们包括矿物、宝石以及石油、煤炭和天然气等能源，这些能源数量有限，不能自然再生。其他不可再生能源包括核燃料和金属矿石。</common:generalComment>
